# {{ title }}

## Detection

High error rate is detected when the ratio of failed requests to total requests exceeds the error budget for service **{{ service_name }}**.

### Alert Triggers
{% if has_error_rate_metric %}
- **Primary**: `{{ metric_by_type.error_rate.metric_name }}` error ratio > 5% for 5 consecutive minutes.
{% else %}
- Monitor error rate through available APM or load-balancer metrics.
{% endif %}
- **Secondary**: Spike in 5xx HTTP status codes from the service.
- **Secondary**: Increase in log ERROR/FATAL frequency.

